### File Structure
```
OnlineAuction/
│
├── app.py
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── auction_catalog.html
│   ├── auction_details.html
│   ├── place_bid.html
│   ├── bid_history.html
│   ├── auction_categories.html
│   ├── winners.html
│   ├── trending_auctions.html
│   └── auction_status.html
│
├── static/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── styles.css
│   ├── js/
│   │   └── scripts.js
│   └── images/
│       └── (auction item images like watch.jpg, iphone.jpg, etc.)
│
└── data/
    ├── auctions.txt
    ├── categories.txt
    ├── bids.txt
    ├── winners.txt
    ├── bid_history.txt
    ├── items.txt
    └── trending.txt
```

### File Descriptions
- **app.py**  
  The main backend Python application file. It will use a web framework like Flask to handle routing, serve pages, process user inputs (e.g., placing bids), read/write data from/to the local text files in the `data/` directory, and implement all business logic for the nine pages. Since the application is not very complex, consolidating backend logic into this single file is efficient and maintainable.

- **templates/**  
  This directory contains all HTML template files for the web application, each corresponding to one of the nine pages described in the requirements. Templates will include the specified elements with their IDs for frontend rendering and interaction.

  - `dashboard.html` — Auction Dashboard page.
  - `auction_catalog.html` — Auction Catalog with search and filter.
  - `auction_details.html` — Detailed view of a specific auction item.
  - `place_bid.html` — Form page for placing a bid.
  - `bid_history.html` — Displays all bids with filtering and sorting.
  - `auction_categories.html` — Lists auction categories.
  - `winners.html` — Shows winning items and winner info.
  - `trending_auctions.html` — Displays trending auctions with filters.
  - `auction_status.html` — Shows status of auctions with refresh.

- **static/**  
  Contains static assets used by the frontend.

  - `css/styles.css` — Stylesheet for consistent styling across pages.
  - `js/scripts.js` — JavaScript for client-side interactivity (e.g., button actions, filtering).
  - `images/` — Folder for auction item images referenced in `auctions.txt`.

- **data/**  
  Stores all application data in text files as specified, used for reading and writing auction, bid, category, winner, and trending information.

This structure cleanly separates backend logic, frontend templates, static assets, and data storage, aligning with the project requirements and enabling straightforward development and maintenance.
